Friedrich Hölderlin,

101
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:25,900
I believe strongly

102
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:29,900
that where there is danger,

103
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:32,900
salvation also grows.

104
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,900
We should inquire

105
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:38,900
whether it,

106
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,900
to what extent,

107
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:44,900
this hope will wait

108
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:48,900
as we explore the possibilities

109
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:51,900
of a culture of life

110
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:54,900
and of a future.

111
00:05:54,900 --> 00:06:00,900
In the face of the real annihilation

112
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:05,900
with which our world is threatened,

113
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,900
I will begin by addressing

114
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:12,900
some of the dangers of our time

115
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:15,900
